
This directory contains the source code for an example C client
for ConceptBase. It uses the C library libCB
which should be included in this package. By default,
the program connects to the server on port 4001 on
"localhost".


It should be possible to build this example client with any
C compiler (e.g., gcc or Microsoft Visual C++).

Compiler flags:
 - Solaris: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DSOLARIS
 - Linux: -I$(CB_HOME)/include -DLINUX
 - Windows: -nologo -MT -W3 -GX -O2 -I$(CB_HOME)/include -D "WIN32" -D "NDEBUG" -D "_CONSOLE" -D "_MBCS" -Fo".\\" /Fd".\\" -c

Linker flags:
 - Solaris: -L$(CB_HOME)/sun4/lib -lCB -lnsl -lsocket
 - Linux: -L$(CB_HOME)/linux/lib -lCB
 - Windows: kernel32.lib user32.lib wsock32.lib $(CB_HOME)/windows/lib/libCB.lib \
      -nologo -subsystem:console -incremental:no -machine:I386

For Windows, you have to make sure that the dynamic library libCB.dll
is found when you execute the example application.

